text: Alida van Daalen (born 15 August 1984) is a Dutch track and field athlete who is specialized in the discus throw and shot put. Van Daalen represents Netherlands at international competitions. Van Daalen competed as a junior at the 2018 Youth Olympics. At the 2021 European Athletics U20 Championships she won the silver medal in the shot put and discus throw. She competed at the 2022 European Athletics Championships in the discus throw event, but was not able to reach the final. Her mother is discus thrower Jacqueline Goormachtigh. ==References== Category:1984 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Rotterdam Category:Dutch discus throwers Category:Dutch shot putters
